computed based on element timestamps and session timeout gaps.\n\n## 5. TimeWindow Class\n**File:** `flink-runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/flink/streaming/api/windowing/windows/TimeWindow.java`\n\n**Class:** `public class TimeWindow extends Window`\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- Constructor: `TimeWindow(long start, long end)` - Creates window with inclusive start and exclusive end timestamps\n- `long getStart()` - Returns window start timestamp\n- `long getEnd()` - Returns window end timestamp (exclusive)\n- `long maxTimestamp()` - Returns `end - 1` (largest timestamp in window)\n- `boolean intersects(TimeWindow other)` - Checks if windows overlap: `this.start <= other.end && this.end >= other.start`\n- `TimeWindow cover(TimeWindow other)` - Returns minimal window covering both: `new TimeWindow(Math.min(start, other.start), Math.max(end, other.end))`\n\n**Utility Method:**\n- `static void mergeWindows(Collection<TimeWindow> windows, MergingWindowAssigner.MergeCallback<TimeWindow> c)` - Implements merging algorithm: sorts windows by start time and merges overlapping windows by invoking callback\n\n**Inner Class:**\n- `Serializer extends TypeSerializerSingleton<TimeWindow>` - Handles serialization of TimeWindow instances (stores two long values: start and end)\n\n## Architecture Summary\n\nFlink's windowing API provides a clean extension point architecture:\n\n1. **WindowAssigner** is the primary extension point where developers define how elements are assigned to windows\n2. **MergingWindowAssigner** extends this for session-style windows that need merging\n3. **Trigger** controls window firing behavior and supports four key lifecycle callbacks\n4. **TimeWindow** is the concrete window implementation for time-based windowing\n5. **EventTimeSessionWindows** demonstrates the complete implementation pattern combining all components\n\nDevelopers implementing custom assigners must provide:\n- Window assignment logic in `assignWindows()`\n- A default trigger in `getDefaultTrigger()`\n- Window serialization support via `getWindowSerializer()`\n- Event/Processing time semantics via `isEventTime()`\n- For merging assigners: implementation of `mergeWindows()` callback"
